{
  "texts": [
    "If you follow the proof of the PAC-Bayesian inequalities seen so far, you will see that the \"bounded loss\" and \"i.i.d.",
    "observations\" assumptions are used only to apply Lemma 1.1 (Hoeffding's inequality) or Lemma 3.8 (Bernstein's inequality).",
    "In other words, in order to prove PAC-Bayes inequalities for unbounded losses or dependent observations, all we need is a result similar to Hoeffding or Bernstein's inequalities (also called exponential moment inequalities) in this context.",
    "In the past 15 years, many variants of PAC-Bayes bounds were developped for various applications based on this remark.",
    "In this section, we provide some pointers."
  ]
}